description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a band 5 nurse to join the Nursing Team on Ward 117 at the Royal Stoke University Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 117 is a 14 bedded Infectious Diseases Unit. The unit manages a wide variety of clinical infections including HIV, TB and travel related infections. We also have close links with the outpatient antibiotic therapy service, the Infection Prevention team, the TB service and the community HIV service. There are excellent learning opportunities in the clinical area and we are currently working closely with the Senior nursing team at the Trust to plan formal development pathways for the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 36 hours per week internal rotation days and nights 12.5 hour shifts. The ideal applicant will have excellent communication skills, a genuine interest in the area of infectious diseases and a willingness to develop their skills within this specialist area of Nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
